  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison had a very uncomfortable train ride from Boston to Syracuse and was much annoyed by the heat, smoke, and dust. Garrison writes: &quot;I have never travelled so rapidly before--averaging at least 35 miles an hour the whole distance.&quot; He stayed with Mr. Wilkinson, whose home he praises. He tells about Samuel Joseph May&apos;s funeral. He went to visit Mr. and Mrs. Wright in Auburn, New York, and will go to see Gerrit Smith after he leaves there.</subfield>
